[normal]2.[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The extent to which those carrying out electrical works are adequately trained to meet the requirements of the B[bold]uilding Regulations and the extent to which all those working for a company are brought up to the same level of skills[bold]&#xa0;[bold]2.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]There are two training routes electrical contractors may take into the industry. However training is just the first step on the path to 
[normal]successful 
[normal]c
[normal]ertification
[normal]. To use an analogy, training and qualification is like taking the driving theory test. The actual driving test assessment with an examiner sitting alongside the candidate is what allows someone to drive a car legally
[normal] and is akin
[normal] to
[normal] the certification assessment of competence.
[normal]  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The traditional route into the industry is a four year apprenticeship with time sp
[normal]lit 
[normal]between academia
[normal] and experience with a sponsoring organisation. On satisfactory completion of studies and an AM2 test
[normal] – a form of practical assessment -
[normal] the apprentice is recognised as an electricia
[normal]n. 
[normal]Originally a
[normal]imed at school leavers
[normal], this route
[normal] is not 
[normal]always 
[normal]realistic or 
[normal]practical for those wishing to change careers
[normal]. As a result, other accelerated routes were develope
[normal]d
[normal]. 
[normal]This
[normal] has caused some dissatisfaction among those who have spent a number of years in the industry
[normal], but it does not mean those routes are without 
[normal]merit
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]All of the qualifications to be eligible to apply for the Part P scheme are detailed in the Minimum 
[normal]Technical Competen
[normal]ce
[normal] (MTC) documents agreed between industry, regulators and Government. 
[normal]This MTC document is also re
[normal]cognised by DECC for the Green Deal S
[normal]chem
[normal]e
[normal]. 
[normal]Since Part P was introduced in 2005, there has been a gradual 
[normal]uplifting 
[normal]of the MTC. From April 
[normal]2013
[normal], the 
[normal]revised electrical MTC 
[normal]will 
[normal]require authorisation and a Level 3 cert
[normal]ificate, which 
[normal]cannot be completed in less than 224 guided learning hours.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.4.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Training and qualifications are set by 
[normal]awarding bodies such as City &amp;
[normal] Guilds and EAL
[normal], the specialist a
[normal]warding organisation for the engineering, building services and related sectors
[normal]. Where Certsure offers training and qualifications they do so under license f
[normal]rom the awarding bodies. Tr
[normal]aining 
[normal]is 
[normal]provided separately from the certification functions to 
[normal]ensure
[normal] that
[normal] independence and impartiality
[normal] is maintained
[normal] 
[normal]and kept under review by 
[normal]the United Kingdom Accreditation Service (
[normal]UKAS
[normal])
[normal]. 
[normal]All surpluses are passed back to the ESC and ECA.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.5.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Once a contractor achieves the correct level of MTC they may apply to be as
[normal]sessed
[normal] for Part P 
[normal]certification
[normal] which costs
[normal] £
[normal]370
[normal]. 
[normal]Assessment recommendations are: pass; pass subject to providing additional evidence; rejection (don’t reapply); and furt
[normal]her assessment to 
[normal]see additional examples of work. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.6.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Over the last 24 months the pass rate 
[normal]has been 81.4%. 6.2% were requested to submit further evidence for review and 12.5% requir
[normal]ed
[normal] an additional visit. The high pass rate is a result of
[normal] a robust pre-assessment process
[normal] which means only those with a good chance of passing put themselves forward 
[normal]or are put forward 
[normal]for assessment.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.7.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Having passed the assessment,
[normal] 
[normal]a 
[normal]Q
[normal]ualified 
[normal]S
[normal]upervisor (QS)
[normal] has ultimate 
[normal]responsibility 
[normal]for signing o
[normal]ff work so in the event that there is an incident caused by bad electrical work the
[normal]y 
[normal]will be held accountable. Certsure 
[normal]makes very clear the consequences for, and responsibilities of, the QS
[normal].  Following a tragic accident 
[normal]in 2007, 
[normal]caused by 
[normal]a contractor failing to test and inspect properly
[normal],
[normal] Certsure
[normal] 
[normal]wrote 
[normal]to every QS
[normal] to remind them of their responsibilities
[normal]. S
[normal]eminars
[normal] are held at industry 
[normal]events
[normal] and NICEIC 
[normal]&amp;
[normal] ELECSA live events to educate and update QSs on their responsibilities. 
[normal]The QS system helps ensure 
[normal]safe working practices are 
[normal]i
[normal]nstitutionalized in a 
[normal]company 
[normal]and 
[normal]not just left to an individual.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.8.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Upon its introductio
[normal]n, Part P 
[normal]cause
[normal]d mixed feelings within the trade, with those who had been involved in the industry for a long time questioning the need to register. However
[normal],
[normal] Certsure is confident that only those contractors who
[normal] can demonstrate their knowledge and understa
[normal]nding of the regulations through a robust assessment will 
[normal]secure certification
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3. [bold]              [bold]The extent to which those carrying out electrical works, to which the Building[bold] [bold]Regulations apply, review or have their work reviewed to ensure that it meets the [bold]requirements of the Regulations[bold]&#xa0;[bold]3.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]All Part P registrants are 
[normal]currently 
[normal]required to be assessed annually through rigorous assessment of their work and knowledge and understanding of the Wiring Regulations. 
[normal]There are over 40,000 contractors registered on Comp
[normal]etent Persons Schemes and their notifiable work is tracked and reported to local authorities. 
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Certsure and its previous entities have undertaken assessments under UKAS accreditation standard EN45011 since 2002
[normal] (NICEIC)
[normal] and 2008
[normal] (ELECSA)
[normal]. 
[normal]We believed thi
[normal]s was essential if contractors were to have fai
[normal]th in the system. Not all Compet
[normal]ent Person Schemes are currently UKAS accredited but they are required to achieve this by
[normal] June
[normal] 2014
[normal] and we welcome this.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Assessments are 
[normal]conducted annually through 
[normal]a minimum o
[normal]f 
[normal]half day of questioning and observation in the presence of a Qualified Supervisor (QS), whose responsibility it is to supervise and sign off the work of others.
[normal] Additional assessment time is required where there 
[normal]are multiple locations
[normal] or additional QSs
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.4.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]A
[normal]ssessment
[normal]s start
[normal] with time spent at the contractor’s office or home 
[normal]where 
[normal]insurance details, complaints system, contracts old and new, electrical certificates, health and safety policy
[normal],
[normal] standards
[normal] 
[normal]and access to appropriate test equipment to carryout test
[normal]ing 
[normal]are reviewed
[normal]. Following this, the assessor and QS will review 
[normal]a 
[normal]sample of work that 
[normal]is
[normal] representative of the contractors work activities
[normal] and are 
[normal]chosen
[normal] by the assessor
[normal]. At each location the assessor will ask question
[normal]s
[normal] of the QS about the installation a
[normal]gainst the written specification and the wiring regulations. The QS will show examples of his work and demonstrate how the installation complies with the
[normal] requirements
[normal]. 
[normal]The QS will also be asked to demonstrate testing and safe isolation.
[normal] 
[normal]We are consiste
[normal]ntly
[normal] reviewing the standards QSs
[normal] need to reach and these have recently been upgraded.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.5.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]Government has previously explored the robustness of the QS system and found it to be satisfactory. 
[normal]Moreover, it means that the Competent Person Scheme covers much more 
[normal]than mere technical competence such as complaints, insurance, health and safety
[normal], management
[normal] etc
[normal].
[normal], unlike GasSafe which solely considers the 
[normal]gas 
[normal]technical competence of the individuals
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.6.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Finally, assessments are conducted by assessors
[normal], the majority of whom
[normal] are electrical engineers
[normal] who are themselves required to have achieved a level of competence in excess of that which they are required to assess. 
[normal]Our 
[normal]a
[normal]ssessors
[normal] 
[normal]are required to update their 
[normal]knowledge on a regular basis
[normal],
[normal] as standards change
[normal]. They do so 
[normal]throu
[normal]gh a mixture of CPD, face to face meetings, regional conferences, technical guidance and
[normal] policy updates
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]The competence of the assessors is reviewed annually by UKAS.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.7.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We have investigated 
[normal]a 
[normal]report 
[normal]in one of the responses 
[normal]of
[normal] 
[normal]a four minute assessment.  
[normal]Our 
[normal]assessment
[normal] report shows that 
[normal]during this assessment 
[normal]we
[normal] assessed a rewire at one address and an additional circuit at another.
[normal] 
[normal]The contractor in question was deregistered from NICEIC for non-payment of fees in February 2012, but unfortunately continues to d
[normal]isplay the NICEIC logo on their website. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.8.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
