[normal]&#xa0;[bold]4.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]UKAS accreditation is only awarded to third party certification bodies that meet and continue to meet the requirements of EN45011. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]EN45011 covers much more than mere technic
[normal]al competence 
[normal]and includes issues such 
[normal]as complaints, insurance 
[normal]governance
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Certification bodies must demonstrate they are independent of any interests that could affect the certification outcome and must be impartial in all of their certification decisi
[normal]ons
[normal]. To achieve this Certsure has a Certification Council made up of industry stakeholders representing users, regulators and the trade. The Council has oversight of certification
[normal] 
[normal]activities and ensures Certsure is independent
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]impartial and operat
[normal]ing
[normal] in a
[normal] way that meets EN45011. 
[normal]The 
[normal]C
[normal]ouncil can raise issues directly with the Certsure Board
[normal] and 
[normal]UKAS as 
[normal]necessary
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.4.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The
[normal] assessment outlined 
[normal]in Section 3 is
[normal] thorough and it 
[normal]is not possible to pass if the c
[normal]ontractor is unable to
[normal] demonstrate how to work safely. Of those undertaking assessment, a number fail
[normal]. They are 
[normal]then offered examples of areas on which they need to improve.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.5.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Furthermore, contractors are required by law to notify 
[normal]s
[normal]cheme operators of any electrical works which 
[normal]they themselves deem as notifiable. T
[normal]his is done v
[normal]ia an online tool which captures t
[normal]he information requested by 
[normal]Local Authority Build
[normal]ing Control and sends 
[normal]this information electronically to the correct L
[normal]ocal 
[normal]A
[normal]uthority
[normal]. 
[normal]A
[normal] certificate
[normal] is then sent
[normal] to the hom
[normal]eowner confirming who did the work and that the contactor has made a declaration that the works comply with Parts 4 and 7 of the Building Regulations. Homeowners may be asked for this information by a conveyancer if they sell their property.   
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.6.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I
[normal]ndependent verification
[normal] of 
