[normal]7. [bold]Conclusions[bold]&#xa0;[bold]7.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The current accreditation scheme,
[normal] built on the 
[normal]1956 model, 
[normal]provides rob
[normal]ust standards for the industry. When the Committee reviewed Part P i
[normal]t stated
[normal]:
[normal] “
[normal]A 
[normal]strengthened Part P Building Regulations regime would be better than a fully mandatory scheme at the present time”. Like 
[normal]the Committee
[normal], we do not believe 
[normal]the review of Part P in 2012 and the reduction of notifications in kitchens and bathrooms 
[normal]will benefit
[normal] electrical safety and may present a real
[normal] safety issue for householders. W
[normal]e do not believe there is any evidence to suggest that the initial conclusion of the 
[normal]Committee
[normal] should be revised.
